<h1>Problem 256 - 2019 AMOC School of Excellence N6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(a\) and \(b\) be two positive integers such that \[b+1 \mid a^2 + 1 \quad \text{ and } \quad a+1 \mid b^2 + 1.\] Prove that both \(a\) and \(b\) are odd.</p>
